Interface ImmutableList<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - type of the contained elements
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Permutations<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractImmutableList, AbstractPermutations, FlatList, ImArrayList, JoinedList, ListWithRemove, MapList, MapThreadList, Outer, PermutationsOrderedWithoutReturn, PermutationsWithoutReturn, PermutationsWithReturn, SessionConfigurationList, ShuffledList, Tuples

    public interface ImmutableList<E>
extends java.lang.Iterable<E>
    Immutable (read-only) list. Implementations are possibly procedural, and can therefore "hold" infinite number of items.
